- Find clear instructions in for how to take the pills in {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "internal", value: {page: "protocol"}} _language="" %}English{% /inlineLink %} and in {% inlineLink action={discriminant: "external", value: {url: "https://es.plancpills.org/protocol", showPopup: false}} _language="" %}Spanish{% /inlineLink %}.
- [HowToUseAbortionPill.org](https://howtouseabortionpill.org) offers instructions in 27 languages. The site also features a live chat for immediate support.

There are also many reliable resources for support:

- The [Miscarriage and Abortion Hotline](https://mahotline.org) provides instructions for taking the pills in English and Spanish, and they offer free confidential support over text or phone.
- The [Reprocare Healthline](https://reprocare.com) connects people with peer counselors and doulas who can support with finding and using the pills, as well as follow-up support.
- The [Aya Contigo](https://ayacontigo.org) app provides live support.
